    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "so you're saying debt reduction is basically the most important thing? i feel like that's a bit of a \"chicken and egg\" problem though. if we cut spending to fix the debt, doesn't that end up hurting growth and making the economy weaker in the long run anyway? wouldn't a stronger social safety net actually make the economy more stable by supporting the people who drive it?",
