      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear that, but it sounds like you're basically saying social programs have to wait until the books are balanced. but what if the \"fiscal framework\" is just an excuse to keep cutting things that people actually need? is it actually \"stable\" to have a balanced budget if half the population is struggling to pay for basic stuff like doctors or housing? isn't that kind of a false choice if you're prioritizing debt over actual human stability?",
